<body>
    <h1>Common Complaints About Subway Sandwiches</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>Bread Quality: Often described as stale, dry, or just plain bad. The bread can also be too thick, making the sandwich hard to eat.</li>
        <li>Meat Selection: Limited and not very high quality. The turkey, for instance, is often criticized for being dry and bland.</li>
        <li>Vegetable Quality: Can be hit or miss. Sometimes fresh and crisp, other times wilted or soggy.</li>
        <li>Portion Sizes: Inconsistent, with some customers feeling they're not getting enough for their money.</li>
        <li>Customization Issues: Difficulty getting sandwiches exactly how they want them, especially with requests for extra or less of certain ingredients.</li>
        <li>Cleanliness: Occasional complaints about the cleanliness of the stores, which can affect the overall dining experience.</li>
        <li>Customer Service: Can vary widely from store to store, with some customers experiencing rude or unhelpful staff.</li>
        <li>Price: Some people feel that the prices are too high for what they're getting, especially when compared to other fast-food options.</li>
    </ul>
</body>
